casebody.data:
No. 09-9751. Dora Olga Cantu Chapa, Petitioner v. United States. 561 U.S. 1021, 130 S. Ct. 3504,

177 L. Ed. 2d 1086,

2010 U.S. LEXIS 5340. June 28, 2010.

Motion of petitioner for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and the petition for a writ of certiorari is granted. The judgment is vacated, and the case is remanded to the United States Court of Appeals for the Fifth Circuit for further consideration in light of Padilla v. Kentucky, 559 U.S. 356, 130 S. Ct. 1473, 176 L. Ed. 2d 284 (2010).

Same case below, 354 Fed. Appx. 203.
